						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the celing of the Lakshmīnarasimhasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription can be assigned to 17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>A verse in <hi rend="italic">Kanda metre</hi> from <hi rend="italic">Rāmaliṅgēśvara śatakaṁ</hi> and states that those who do not perform any <hi rend="italic">dāna</hi> and dhārma cannot live in this earth happily.</p>						

